<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>MySQL is not case sensitive with WHERE querys.
But if I need for example a exact comparison where "ABC" != "abc" like on passwords,
it would be great to add a option that declares weather the where clause is case sensitive or not (on Zend_Validate_Db_NoRecordExists or Zend_Validate_Db_RecordExists).</p>

    </div>
